
<p>Don't fret. You WILL fix it. We will help.</p>

<h2 id="fixingcommonproblems">Fixing Common Mistakes</h2>

<ul>
  <li><a href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/bad_solder_joint.html">Bad solder joint</a></li>
  <li><a href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/misplaced_component.html">Misplaced component</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="unsureoftheproblem">Unsure of the Problem?</h2>
<p>Let's look at the clues to figure out what's going on with your pedal. Before we continue, though, <strong>if your LED won't light then UNPLUG</strong> your pedal for now. If you have a power issue it's better to limit the time the circuit is exposed to the wrong power supply.</p>
<p><strong>Follow this flowchart</strong> to find the most likely cause of common problems. Or <strong>skip past it to <a href="#getpersonalhelp">learn about our support forum</a></strong>.</p>

[% BLOCK visit_forum %]
<p><small>If that doesn't help, <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/maseffects/" target="_blank">visit our forum</a> and provide some pictures and details and we'll help you figure out what's going on.</small></p>
[% END %]
<div class="flowchart">
  <h3>Step 1</h3>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-12 question">
      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        Is the problem <strong>sporadic</strong> / occassional?
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary">Yes</span>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary">No</span>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
        <h6 class="probable_cause">Probable cause:</h6>
        <div class="text-start">
          <p>You probably have one or more <a href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/bad_solder_joint.html">bad solder joints</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/bad_solder_joint.html">FIX IT</a></p>
        <div class="text-start">
          [% INCLUDE visit_forum %]
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        <p>The problem is constant</p>
        <p><strong>Continue to step 2</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Step 2</h3>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-12 question">
      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        Pushing the foot switch toggles between engaged and bypassed.
        Are you getting a <strong>clean bypassed sound</strong> in one of the positions?
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary">Yes</span>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary">No</span>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        <p>A clean bypassed signal can be heard</p>
        <p><strong>Continue to step 3</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6 answer">

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
        <h6 class="probable_cause">Probable cause:</h6>
        <div class="text-start">
          <p>If you can never hear sound pass through your pedal, it's likely one or more <a href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/bad_solder_joint.html">bad solder joints</a> on the <a href="/quickfuzz/assemble/install_ftsw.html">foot switch</a> or the <a href="/quickfuzz/assemble/install_jacks.html">phone jacks</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/bad_solder_joint.html">FIX IT</a></p>
        <div class="text-start">
          <p>If you overheated your foot switch, it may also be damaged. If your joints look good, <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/maseffects/" target="_blank">visit our support forum</a> for tips on diagnosing the foot switch.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Step 3</h3>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-12 question">
      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        When the pedal is <strong>engaged</strong>, what do you hear?
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary">Something, but it's not right</span>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary">Silence</span>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"><i class="fas fa-down-long"></i></div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
        <h6 class="probable_cause">Probable cause:</h6>
        <div class="text-start">
          <p><small>If you get sound from your pedal, but find the volume is too quiet, not distorted enough, or too filtered...</small></p>
          <p>
            The problem is likely
            a <strong><a href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/misplaced_component.html">misplaced component</a></strong>.
          </p>
        </div>
          <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/misplaced_component.html">FIX IT</a></p>
        <div class="text-start">
          <p>It could possibly be a <a href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/bad_solder_joint.html">bad solder joint</a> as well.</p>
          [% INCLUDE visit_forum %]
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        <p>The pedal has a clean signal when bypassed, but no output when engaged.</p>
        <p><strong>Continue to step 4</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Step 4</h3>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-12 question">
      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        Does the <strong>LED light up</strong> when engaged?
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary">Yes</span>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary">No</span>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"><i class="fas fa-down-long"></i></div>
    <div class="col-6 flow"> <i class="fas fa-down-long"></i> </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
        <h6 class="probable_cause">Probable cause:</h6>
        <div class="text-start">
          <p>
          Your cables may be reversed.
          </p>
        </div>
        <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/no_distortion.html">FIX IT</a></p>
        <div class="text-start">
          [% INCLUDE visit_forum %]
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-6">
      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
        <h6 class="probable_cause">Probable cause:</h6>
        <div class="text-start">
          <p>
          You probably have some sort of a power-related problem.
          </p>
        </div>
        <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/quickfuzz/troubleshooting/power.html">FIX IT</a></p>
        <div class="text-start">
          [% INCLUDE visit_forum %]
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>


